related cognitive deficits in patients after hematopoietic stem cell transplantation
Participants 314 713 9
One hundred fifty-seven patients were screened for cognitive deficits following HSCT for malignant diseases at an in-patient oncologic rehabilitation clinic. Patients showing evidence of impairment were randomly assigned to one of two training groups: individualized PC-supported training or neuropsychological group therapy. The control group consisted of patients who received no specific training
